# ScrapCo V2 — Non-Functional Requirements (NFR)

## 1. NFR Philosophy

Non-functional requirements define system quality.

ScrapCo V2 must not only work — it must be:

- Reliable
- Secure
- Scalable
- Performant
- Observable
- Maintainable
- Resilient
- Auditable

Functional features are secondary to system stability.

---

## 2. Performance Requirements

### 2.1 API Performance

- P95 response time < 300ms
- P99 response time < 800ms
- Authentication middleware overhead < 50ms
- DB query latency < 100ms for indexed queries

---

### 2.2 Dispatch Performance

- Assignment time (P95) < 5 minutes
- Offer creation latency < 2 seconds
- Expiry handling delay < 5 seconds
- Worker job processing concurrency supported

---

### 2.3 Web Performance

- Lighthouse Performance > 90
- LCP < 2.5 seconds
- TTFB < 500ms
- CLS < 0.1
- INP within acceptable threshold

---

### 2.4 Mobile Performance

- Smooth performance on low-end Android
- No UI freeze > 200ms
- Push notification latency < 10 seconds
- No polling loops

---

## 3. Scalability Requirements

System must support:

- 10x traffic growth without redesign
- Horizontal API scaling
- Horizontal worker scaling
- Multi-city expansion
- Multi-region vendor pools
- Concurrent dispatch processing

Dispatch must not depend on:

- Single process memory
- Single worker instance

---

## 4. Reliability Requirements

- API uptime ≥ 99%
- Worker restart does not lose dispatch state
- Redis failure does not corrupt DB
- Database backup enabled
- Health check endpoint required

No silent failure allowed.

---

## 5. Availability Requirements

- Deployment without downtime
- Graceful shutdown support
- Retry logic for transient failures
- Circuit breaker pattern (optional Phase 2)

System must degrade gracefully under load.

---

## 6. Security Requirements

Must ensure:

- JWT-based authentication
- Role-based authorization
- HMAC-secured webhooks
- Rate limiting
- Strict CORS
- No environment flag-based admin
- No public vendor write endpoints
- Secret rotation support

No exposed service-role keys.

---

## 7. Data Integrity Requirements

System must:

- Prevent duplicate assignment
- Prevent expired offer acceptance
- Enforce region match
- Enforce one transaction per pickup
- Maintain immutable transaction records
- Log all state transitions

All financial data must be auditable.

---

## 8. Maintainability Requirements

Codebase must:

- Use strict TypeScript
- Follow modular architecture
- Avoid duplicated logic
- Use centralized validation
- Have clear folder structure
- Include test coverage for core logic
- Avoid dead code

Code must be readable and reviewable.

---

## 9. Testability Requirements

Minimum:

- Unit tests for dispatch logic
- Unit tests for auth middleware
- Integration tests for pickup lifecycle
- Validation tests for input schemas

CI must fail if tests fail.

---

## 10. Observability Requirements

Must include:

- Structured logs
- Correlation IDs
- Error tracking
- Dispatch metrics
- Vendor acceptance metrics
- Assignment time metrics
- Revenue tracking

No blind deployment.

---

## 11. Compliance & Audit Requirements

System must:

- Log all admin actions
- Log commission changes
- Log assignment changes
- Store audit logs permanently
- Support export of financial records

No record deletion of financial data allowed.

---

## 12. Configuration Requirements

- All environment variables validated at startup
- No fallback to insecure defaults
- No production config stored in code
- Clear separation of staging and production

Misconfigured environment must fail fast.

---

## 13. Resilience Requirements

System must handle:

- Worker crash
- Redis restart
- Database temporary unavailability
- Vendor webhook failure
- Network spikes

Dispatch must resume safely.

---

## 14. Extensibility Requirements

Architecture must allow:

- Competitive vendor model
- Wallet system
- Payment integration
- Recycler integration
- Multi-language support
- Analytics microservice
- AI dispatch optimization

Without structural rewrite.

---

## 15. Accessibility Requirements

Web:

- WCAG AA compliance
- Keyboard navigable
- Screen reader friendly
- Reduced motion support

Mobile:

- Accessibility labels
- Scalable text
- High contrast support

---

## 16. Backup & Recovery Requirements

- Daily DB backups
- Restore testing plan
- Redis persistence configured
- Disaster recovery documentation

Recovery must not require manual DB rebuild.

---

## 17. Deployment Requirements

- Automated CI/CD
- Zero manual production SSH
- Health check endpoints required
- Rollback support
- Versioned releases

---

## 18. Prohibited Practices

System must never:

- Use polling for lifecycle
- Use in-memory dispatch state
- Use environment flag admin access
- Hardcode region logic
- Skip validation
- Log secrets
- Deploy without monitoring
- Ignore error spikes

---

## 19. Success Criteria

ScrapCo V2 meets NFR when:

- Stable under 10x simulated load
- Dispatch consistent
- No critical security findings
- No duplicate assignments
- No revenue mismatch
- Observability dashboards operational
- CI pipeline reliable

---

## 20. Summary

Non-functional requirements ensure ScrapCo V2 is:

- Production-grade
- Scalable
- Secure
- Reliable
- Observable
- Maintainable

If NFRs are violated, feature work must pause until resolved.
```
